  <p style="font-size:8.2pt;color:#5a4a54;margin:8px 0 0"><b>Assessment.</b> Base case is a contested, partly-restored order with a formal model-export regime taking shape over 12–24 months. The decisive near-term signal is whether a second lab receives a comparable directive; that would move the pessimistic scenario from tail risk to base case. As of 14 June, active resolution talks (Axios) tilt the near term toward the optimistic, targeted-measure scenario. Monitor the Aunoo sentiment-inflection indicator for a negative turn.</p>

  <h2 class="sec">Outlook &amp; indicators to watch</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><b>Restoration vs. escalation:</b> whether Commerce rescinds/narrows the order, or formalises a lasting model-level export regime.</li>
    <li><b>Documentation:</b> release of specifics on the jailbreak would shift the credibility balance between government and Anthropic.</li>
    <li><b>Spillover to rivals:</b> similar action against OpenAI/Google models would confirm a doctrine, not a one-off.</li>
    <li><b>Legal challenge:</b> likely, given Anthropic's prior willingness to litigate the supply-chain designation.</li>
    <li><b>International response:</b> concrete sovereign-AI funding/announcements (India, Gulf states, EU) in coming weeks.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="sec">Source assessment &amp; confidence</h2>
  <p>Findings are anchored on the <b>primary source</b> (Anthropic's own statement [1]) and consistently reported by US wire and tech press (AP [2], Ars Technica [3]) and across regions: Hong Kong (SCMP [6]), Australia (Sydney Morning Herald [9]), France (France 24 [8]), Russia (TASS), plus Politico [5] and Boston Globe [7]. The jailbreak is <b>independently documented</b> [4]. The Amazon-trigger account is <b>single-sourced to the Wall Street Journal</b> [10], and the link between the public jailbreak and the government's stated concern is <b>inferred, not cited</b>. Aggregate sentiment is Neutral (Aunoo consensus: 70/15/15).</p>
  <p><b>Confidence:</b> High on the order and its terms (primary-sourced, broadly corroborated) and on the jailbreak demonstration (independently documented). Moderate on the <i>cause</i>, pending the government's technical justification, given two reported triggers and no official attribution to the public demonstration.</p>

